right vertical joining the diagonal above the line; omicron is small and mid-line.",[47,53],{"type":48,"l":49,"from":50,"to":50,"h":51,"unit":52,"atLeast":51,"atMost":51},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","30","mm",{"type":54,"l":55,"from":50,"to":56,"h":57,"unit":52},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2","NA",{"_":59,"notBefore":60,"notAfter":61,"evidence":62},"The tomb has not been excavated fully, but the cemetery went out of use around the end of the 3rd century BCE or early 2nd century, offering a terminus ante quem",-350,-201,"archaeological-context",[64,69],{"_":65,"type":66,"ref":67,"corresp":68},"Abacaenum","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462062","#findspot",{"_":8,"type":70,"ref":71,"offset":72},"modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2522853","near",[74],[75,76],38.05191,15.10158,[13,14],"Italy","Sicily",{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"type":82},"inventory",{"_":84,"mainLang":85,"languages":86},"Ancient Greek","grc",[84],{"n":88,"url":89,"height":90,"width":91,"desc":92,"surfaceType":93},"screen","ISic004415_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","front",[95],{"atLeast":96,"atMost":96},30,[98,99],"Bacci, Coppolino, 2009, La Necropoli di Abakainon: primi dati","Sofia, 2018, Nuove iscrizioni funerarie dalla necropoli di Abakainon",[101,102],"DX8AWC9Q","JQQKI6JP",[104,105,106,26,30,34,107,108,109,110,108,111,112,85],"isic004415","epitaph for krimma, child of aunakos",{"_":23},"abacaenum","tripi","italy","sicily","necropoli di abakainon","ancient greek","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Κριμμα Αυνακου \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"file":115,"uri":115,"title":116,"status":117,"editionAuthor":24,"type":118,"objectType":119,"material":120,"condition":10,"layoutDesc":121,"handNote":125,"date":131,"places":132,"geo":135,"provenance":65,"provenanceGeo":137,"country":78,"region":79,"settlement":8,"repository":138,"idno":139,"textLang":140,"tmNumber":10,"facsimile":142,"letterHeights":144,"publications":147,"zotero":148,"keywords":149,"html":153},"ISic004416","Epitaph for Philon, son Aunakos",{"_":23},{"_":26,"ana":27,"ref":28},{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},{"_":34,"ana":35,"ref":36},{"layout":122},{"p":123,"rs":124,"damage":10},"Single line of greek letters approximately centred on the face of the plinth, descending to right",{"_":41,"ana":42,"ref":43},{"lettering":126,"dimensions":127},"Crude and irregularly carved large letters. Phi has a small eye, seemingly formed of two small loops; omega is small, mid-line, open, with outward/downward sloping tails; nu is large and uneven; alpha is broad, but the form of the bar is illegible; kappa has short equal arms joined to the vertical; omicron appears small and midline.",[128,130],{"type":48,"l":49,"from":50,"to":50,"h":129,"unit":52,"atLeast":129,"atMost":129},"59",{"type":54,"l":55,"from":50,"to":56,"h":57,"unit":52},{"_":59,"notBefore":60,"notAfter":61,"evidence":62},[133,134],{"_":65,"type":66,"ref":67,"corresp":68},{"_":8,"type":70,"ref":71,"offset":72},[136],[75,76],[13,14],{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"type":82},{"_":84,"mainLang":85,"languages":141},[84],{"n":88,"url":143,"height":90,"width":91,"desc":92,"surfaceType":93},"ISic004416_tiled.tif",[145],{"atLeast":146,"atMost":146},59,[98,99],[101,102],[150,151,152,26,30,34,107,108,109,110,108,111,112,85],"isic004416","epitaph for philon, son aunakos",{"_":23},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Φίλων Αυ̣νακου \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"file":155,"uri":155,"title":156,"status":157,"editionAu